<ns3677:para xmlns:ns3677="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.technologies.java.j2ee.jdbc.drivers.classes.introParagraph">

    
  There are 4 distinct JDBC driver classes. Choosing a particular class of JDBC driver
  has implications on performance and on the portability of the driver. The 4 classes of JDBC
  drivers are
  
  <ns3678:itemizedlist xmlns:ns3678="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns3679:listitem xmlns:ns3679="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns3680:para xmlns:ns3680="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      <ns3681:emphasis xmlns:ns3681="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Class 1 JDBC drivers</ns3681:emphasis>  use a JDBC-ODBC bridge.
    </ns3680:para></ns3679:listitem>
    <ns3682:listitem xmlns:ns3682="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns3683:para xmlns:ns3683="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      <ns3684:emphasis xmlns:ns3684="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Class 2 JDBC drivers</ns3684:emphasis>  use a JDBC-DBMS client library bridge.
    </ns3683:para></ns3682:listitem>
    <ns3685:listitem xmlns:ns3685="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns3686:para xmlns:ns3686="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      <ns3687:emphasis xmlns:ns3687="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Class 3 JDBC drivers</ns3687:emphasis>  are pure Java JDBC drivers which interact
      with a JDBC server which directly communicates with the database engine API.
    </ns3686:para></ns3685:listitem>
    <ns3688:listitem xmlns:ns3688="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns3689:para xmlns:ns3689="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      <ns3690:emphasis xmlns:ns3690="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Class 4 JDBC drivers</ns3690:emphasis> are pure Java driver which communicate 
      directly with the database through the native communication protocol used by the database. 
    </ns3689:para></ns3688:listitem>
  </ns3678:itemizedlist>
</ns3677:para>